<paragraph id="8BEF36EAFFA8FF9DFF259F2AE379A2F8" blockId="12.[151,1436,319,704]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFA8FF9DFF259F2AE003A110" author="Vayssiere" box="[151,343,319,343]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Vayssiere, P. (1923) Un nouveau coccide (Hem.) de la faune Africaine. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 11 / 12, 152 - 55." type="journal article" year="1923">
Vayssière (
<number id="3D9824CDFFA8FF9DFEA79F2AE01BA110" box="[277,335,319,343]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1923.0">1923</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the adult female, adult male and first-instar nymph of this species from the Aurès mountains of 
<collectingCountry id="F347767AFFA8FF9DFE869F71E0DCA13B" box="[308,392,356,380]" name="Algeria" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Algeria</collectingCountry>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFE069F70E3DBA13B" box="[436,655,356,380]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thurifera">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFE069F70E3DBA13B" box="[436,655,356,380]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Juniperus thurifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFD2D9F71E26BA13B" box="[671,831,356,380]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cupressaceae</taxonomicName>
). The generic and family placement of this species is problematic because it possesses characteristics of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFCB99F9CE214A1E7" box="[779,832,393,416]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFCB99F9CE214A1E7" box="[779,832,393,416]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFCC49F9DE28AA1D8" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[886,990,392,415]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFCC49F9DE28AA1D8" box="[886,990,392,415]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ceroputo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as understood here. The presence of 
<number id="3D9824CDFFA8FF9DFA329F92E4C8A1D8" box="[1408,1436,391,415]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="12.0">12</number>
eyes on the adult male, seven-segmented antennae on the first-instar nymph and, on the adult female, basal spurs on the claw, tubular ducts on the frons, and three sensilla on each surface of the trochanter, are features consistent with species of 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFEF49FE0E0D6A24B" box="[326,386,501,524]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFEF49FE0E02AA24B" box="[326,382,501,524]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Puto</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The absence of multilocular pores and the presence of quinquelocular pores are features consistent with species of 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFE279C0DE352A268" box="[405,518,536,559]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFE279C0DE355A268" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[405,513,536,559]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ceroputo</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The similarity of this species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFCC79C0DE50CA277" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[885,1112,536,560]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nulliporus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFCC79C0DE50CA277" box="[885,1112,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ceroputo nulliporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFB3D9C0DE459A277" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[1167,1293,536,560]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimicus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFB3D9C0DE459A277" box="[1167,1293,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. mimicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFA8FF9DFF569C28E36FA213" author="Marotta" box="[228,571,572,596]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Marotta, S. &amp; Tranfaglia, A. (1993) Le specie del genere Puto Signoret (Homoptera Coccoidea Pseudococcidae) del'Europa centrale e del bacino del Mediterraneo. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria ' Filippo Silvestri', Portici, 48, 171 - 205." type="journal article" year="1993">
Marotta and Tranfaglia (
<number id="3D9824CDFFA8FF9DFE449C29E367A213" box="[502,563,572,596]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. We here retain this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFC209C28E293A213" box="[914,967,573,596]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFC209C28E293A213" box="[914,967,573,596]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it possesses more features of this genus than of 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFA8FF9DFE849C75E0F1A230" box="[310,421,608,631]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFA8FF9DFE849C75E0F5A230" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[310,417,608,631]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ceroputo</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but further investigations are required. We agree with the illustration of this species given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFA8FF9DFF089C90E35AA2DB" author="Marotta" box="[186,526,644,668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Marotta, S. &amp; Tranfaglia, A. (1993) Le specie del genere Puto Signoret (Homoptera Coccoidea Pseudococcidae) del'Europa centrale e del bacino del Mediterraneo. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria ' Filippo Silvestri', Portici, 48, 171 - 205." type="journal article" year="1993">
Marotta and Tranfaglia (
<number id="3D9824CDFFA8FF9DFE7E9C91E352A2DB" box="[460,518,644,668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but provide corrected information on the tubular duct distribution and number of sensilla on the trochanter in Table 
<number id="3D9824CDFFA8FF9DFDAA9CB2E373A2F8" box="[536,551,679,703]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
